    • Method Detail

      • search

        public AddressInfo search(AddressInfo findMe)
        Invokes the contain method on the HashSet with the argument findMe in order to check to see if the AddressInfo object findMe is in the database.
        Parameters:
        findMe - an AddressInfo object to be searched for
        Returns:
        null if the object is in the HashSet, returns the current AddressInfo object if it equals findMe, or null for any other situation

      • add

        public boolean add(AddressInfo addMe)
        Invokes the contains method on myHashSet to check for a duplicate record, if a duplicate is found, add returns false. If no duplicate is found then the add method is invoked on the HashSet with an argument equal to the addMe parameter
        Parameters:
        addMe - the AddressInfo object to be searched for and added if it is not already in the database
        Returns:
        false if the HashSet already contains addme, true if the object doesn't already exist

      • delete

        public boolean delete(AddressInfo deleteMe)
        delete method Invokes the contains method on the HashSet if the item is not in the database, it returns false, if it does exist, then delete invokes the remove method on the hashSet using deleteMe as a parameter
        Parameters:
        deleteMe - the AddressInfo item to be searched for and deleted if it exists in the database
        Returns:
        false if the object doesn't exist, true if the object is removed successfully

      • toStringAlphabetical

        public java.lang.String toStringAlphabetical()
        Constructs a local TreeSet named myAlpha with no argument. Invokes the addAll method on the myAlpha using the HashSet as an argument
        Returns:
        the string that was returned by invoking toString on the TreeSet

      • toStringByAddress

        public java.lang.String toStringByAddress()
        Constructs a local TreeSet named myAddress with the public static final Comparator object as an argument. Invokes addAll method on myAddress using the HashSet as an argument
        Returns:
        the string that was returned by invoking toString on the TreeSet

      • saveToFile

        public java.lang.String saveToFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        saves the current HashSet to a file by invoking the iterator method on the HashSet to get an iterator object, uses a while loop with the iterator to traverse the HashSet and writes each traversed object to the ObjectOutputStream
        Parameters:
        fileName - a string to name the file
        Returns:
        an empty string if all goes well, otherwise an error message is returned

      • loadFromFile

        public java.lang.String loadFromFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        Each object comes from the file and is inserted into the HashSet using the add method
        Parameters:
        fileName - the name of the file to be loaded
        Returns:
        empty string if all goes well, or an error if not
